        "title": "Drink-up — Lessons From 10 years of Platform Engineering",
        "excerpt":"This event is a memorial gathering, a wake to the planned — but now cancelled — DevOpsDays Copenhagen 2026.   The event is free to participate - SEATS ARE LIMITED TO 40!   Venue        Venue    The Workbar         Matrikel 1, Gammel Strand 26, Copenhagen                   Website                 Map           Program   We start 17:00 sharp 🎯 — arrive and be seated in due time before that!      Welcome + 1 minute of silence for the deceased DevOpsDays   Lessons from 10 years of Platform Engineering by Kris Buytaert   Table discussions — “What the heck is going on in the DevOps Community right now?”   Summary on table discussions   Outro — The current status of the transformed Danish DevOpsDays Association and a glimpse into what the future will bring   It ends at the “Workbar” no later than 19:00 but if we’re still a decent crowd we will continue onward for a burger or a pizza.   Keynote:   …flying in from Belgium to deliver his planned Keynote:                                                                                                Kris Buytaert        Principal Yak Shaver o11y.eu                                                                                                           Lessons From 10 years of Platform Engineering                                                                                   Post Mortem:   We had to cancel the planned two-day DevOpsDays conference, simply due to lack of interest from audience. This is the canary in coal mine; DevOps(Days) choked. Let’s do a post mortem. Platform Engineering is the new DevOps — so we’re told. “No — that’s Ops, not DevOps”. Where did all the “You Build It You Run It” hype go? We will kick off discussions on this topic at the tables - while you sip your funeral beer.   Phoenix rising:   The Danish DevOpsDays Association has a new charter, new bylaws, a new purpose. We, the organizers, will lay out our plans for the future and encourage you to join.   Context:   DevOps is Broken  ","categories": [],
